The paper deals with cross-technology communication between LTE-U and WiFi networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of radio resource management (RRM) and interference management, which could fall under cs.IT (information theory) and cs.CR (cryptography and security). Additionally, the paper involves the implementation and evaluation of a prototype, which could fall under cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.COM (computer communication networks).
